reviews.message: My 14-year-old son was struggling with regular subsitute teachers in school, but Nathan was excellent at really explaining how maths worked to Aaron in an engaging way. He really made the subject interesting!

Nathan pushed me to get As in my Nat5 exams. I learned lots of new techniques that I couldn't get at school. He really explained the more difficult ideas in depth and gave real life examples for them, which was useful.
Nathan helped me for a few weeks before my higher prelims with what to expect from the exams. I learned different skills and gained confidence in my mental maths.
